      "title": "[DC] far0w1@🔸有問必答┊official-q-a: As a slay the spire player the dtide is really the least roguelite mode there is",
      "summary": "As a slay the spire player the dtide is really the least roguelite mode there is, which is fine for an end game mode but not when there are upgrade and gear mode behind it. Fine if I have to play the mode at least allow us to auto farm it, so I can get the materials for account progression and play the mode I like for example the new train mode.\n\nI actually don’t like either the dive or the dtide especially when there is forced exploration without stories, without enough rng and deck-building these mode feel very repetitive and not really like the challenges you see in slay the spire. With upgrade materials gated behind end game it’s a catch 22 situation.",
